cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.TL, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a calculus for classical arithmetic and discusses the normalization and soundness of the calculus. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of control operators and lazy evaluation in the calculus. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possibility as the paper deals with the encoding of functions into streams. 
- cs.TL (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are less likely categories as they are not directly related to the content of the paper.
